sec.p:
Ultrafine particle number counts and size distributions in Hong Kong need to be monitored to better understand how human exposure can vary temporally and with the source contributors and this could also have an important impact on exposures in homes [14–16]. The dispersion of fine particles in a street canyon in Hong Kong has been described [17]. In this study, number concentrations and size distributions of particles with sizes ranging from 7 to 2,000 nm were investigated at a roadside environment in Hong Kong. The aims of the study were to


investigate the diurnal and seasonal variations of particle number concentrations;

characterize the size distributions of particle number, mass, volume and surface;

explore the relationships of particle number concentrations and aerosol loadings and

identify dominant factors and sources that influence the variability of ultrafine particles.
